<H3>NORML Reports</H3>

<H2>A Citizens Guide to the Drug Laws </H2>
Published Oct. 1994<BR>
Updated May/June 2000<BR>
by Chuck Thomas, NORML Publications Director<P>

<OL TYPE=I><LI><A HREF="lawwara.tpl"><B>WAR AGAINST MARIJUANA CONSUMERS</B></A><BR>

There is a common misconception that the government does not aggressively pursue recreational marijuana consumers. The arrest statistics clearly show otherwise.<P>

<LI><A HREF="lawrigh.tpl"><B>KNOW AND EXERCISE YOUR RIGHTS</B></A><BR>
Most marijuana consumers either do not understand or do not exercise their legal rights. <P>

<LI><A HREF="lawstat.tpl"><B>STATE-BY-STATE LISTING</B></A><BR>
A listing of the penalties that apply to certain marijuana crimes in each of the 50 states and the District of Colombia, as well as the applicable federal penalties
- compiled by Alison Green, Staff Assistant<P>

<LI><A HREF="lawextr.tpl"><B>EXTREME MEASURES</B></A><BR>
As part of the government's campaign of terror against marijuana consumers, many bizarre penalties and practices have been implemented.<P>

<LI><A HREF="lawincr.tpl"><B>INCREASE YOUR KNOWLEDGE</B></A><BR>
Do not limit yourself to the information contained here.

</OL>
special thanks to NORML interns Tom Wright and Derek Barker for extensive research assistance
<P><BR>



<B>NORML believes that the decision to consume marijuana is a personal one
that should not be dictated by law.</B>  NORML supports the removal of all
penalties for the private possession of marijuana, cultivation for personal
use, and casual non-profit transfers of small amounts by adults.  NORML
supports reasonable regulations for large-scale cultivation and distribution,
and reasonable restrictions on driving under the influence, consumption by
minors, and smoking in public places.  The national office, state affiliates
and local chapters work diligently to reform marijuana laws.<P>
<B>NORML does not, however, advocate nor encourage the consumption of marijuana or
any other drugs.</B>  NORML believes that the current laws are unjust and that
millions of Americans have already made the personal decision to consume
marijuana in violation of the law.  Therefore, NORML believes that it is
important to distribute information about the applicable laws.<P>
<B>This report is not "legal advice."</B>  Legal advice can only be provided by an
attorney to his or her clients.  The information contained herein is simply a
compilation of public information about federal and state marijuana laws and
various constitutionally guaranteed rights.  This report is the result of
hundreds of hours of research by NORML interns and staff, and it has been
examined and reviewed by members of the NORML Legal Committee.<P>
<B>Nevertheless, NORML bears absolutely no responsibility for the accuracy, use,
misuse, or abuse of the information contained herein.</B>  As long as marijuana
consumption remains a crime, NORML can only recommend that concerned citizens
fight together to change the laws.  Violation of the current laws can only be
undertaken at one's own risk.<P>
